title: For Sale:  SKS takes AK47 mags like Paratrooper model D  M
postcontent: If This Listing Is Still Up Then I Still Have it....................Here is a nice Norinco SKS that has been professionally machined by a top notch gunsmith to take AK47 magazines. It works perfectly. It also has been shortened like the paratrooper model with a muzzle brake installed and all of the bayonet junk has been neatly removed. This makes it a fairly light and handy rifle. Everything works perfectly. Note - You loose the last-round hold-open function when you do this but most AKs notoriously do not have last round hold open either. This will group nicely with standard low-end steel cased Russian ammo. Of course it would be even better with good ammo and also an SKS will shoot more accurately than most AK47s.  BTW - At my age my eyes and iron sights are not a good thing anymore. This is an all numbers matching except the dust cover on rear which was replaced. The pictures do not show it but the receiver has 3 screw holes where a side mounted scope was installed once-upon-a-time. These holes have flush mounted screws with lock tight. Its a neat job but it is there and I don't want anyone to be surprised by this slight cosmetic issue. It comes with everything pictured. It has 2 good stocks and the black "cheese grater" gas tube cover works well for both. The colors of the camo in the picture did not come out true(base is coyote tan then OD green with some foliage green) but it is a nice three colors and the paracord braided sling matches it well. The camo stock has a slip on butt pad as pictured. The other stock has a pro installed slightly longer pad and comes with the standard SKS sling. These 1" and 1"+ extensions just feel a little better as these chicomm stocks that are usually a little bit short. They both come up nice to your shoulder. This comes with a high quality case that holds everything. It also comes with the old mil surplus mag pouch pictured that has 2 more 20 round magazines in it making a total of 3 20s included in the sale. It takes 30s too of course. I just prefer 20s. It also comes with the maglula AK47 magazine loader still in package and one extra butt pad that - uh well I never liked it but you might find some use for?. I am asking $590 for all of it. Add it up. This is a great deal. I check email often. This will be available thru Saturday 5/12 only.  This will be FTF and green cash only probably in a parking lot somewhere around the 1200 N. Walton area in Bentonville. We'll work out details of a meet in email. title: For Sale:  Finnish Mosin Rare
postcontent: This is a very rare Finnish M91 B-barrel. The B is for belgium which is where finnish sourced all of the barrels from. Finnish mosins are the rarest variation of mosin nagants because of their very low production numbers compared to other countries. This rifle is dated 1942, all B-barrel M91s were assembled after the war so most are in good shape. Production lasted from 1940-42 and total production was 4000-5000 making them extremely rare. Bluing is 75-80%, barrel looks brand new probably fired very little, stock is perfect no cracks. Asking 600 Obo, feel free to txt REDACTED.
